<div class="xar-mod-body">
     <xar:template type="module" file="admin-menu" />
   <img src="#xarTplGetImage('admin_generic.gif', 'base')#" alt="official icon" width="96" height="96" class="xar-module-icon" />
    <h2>
        <xar:mlstring>Overview</xar:mlstring>
    </h2>
    <h3>
            <xar:mlstring>What is it?</xar:mlstring>
    </h3>
        <p><em><xar:mlstring>Categories is a Xaraya Utility Module.</xar:mlstring></em>
            <xar:mlstring>It is currently responsible for accomplishing these tasks:</xar:mlstring>
            <ul>
                <li><xar:mlstring>Allows the use of site wide categories for content modules to use as needed.</xar:mlstring></li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <h3>
            <xar:mlstring>How to use it?</xar:mlstring>
       </h3>
        <p><xar:mlstring>From the menu, you have two choices.  'Add a New Category', and 'View Categories'.</xar:mlstring>
            <ul>
                <li><xar:mlstring>Add a new category -- Allows you to add a new category to your site categories tree.</xar:mlstring></li>
                <li><xar:mlstring>View Categories -- This area allows you to view the entire categorization tree, allowing a easy way to modify it.</xar:mlstring></li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <h3>
            <xar:mlstring>Included Blocks</xar:mlstring>
        </h3>
        <p>
            <xar:mlstring>The Navigation block allows navigation of any module using the category hooks.</xar:mlstring>
        </p>
         <h3>
            <xar:mlstring>Included Hooks</xar:mlstring>
    </h3>
        <p>
            <xar:mlstring>Categories provides all the hooks necessary to allow categories to be available within other modules.</xar:mlstring>
        </p>
        <h3><xar:mlstring>Further Information</xar:mlstring></h3>
    <p>
       <xar:mlstring>Extended information about this module can be found at </xar:mlstring><a title="#xarML('Categories Module - Xaraya Extension 147')#" href="http://www.xaraya.com/index.php/release/147.html">Xaraya Extension and Releases</a>.
       </p>
      <ul>
          <li><xar:mlstring>Click on Version History tab at the bottom to get the latest release information.</xar:mlstring>
          </li>
          <li><xar:mlstring>Related tutorials and documentation on Categories found at</xar:mlstring> <a href="http://www.xaraya.com/index.php/keywords/categories/" title="#xarML('Related documentation on Categories')#"><xar:mlstring>Xaraya Documentation.</xar:mlstring></a>
          </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="xar-sub">
